mology, it may represent an Anglicized form of any of several Irish names containing the element <i>gall</i> ‘stranger’, e.g.   Doyle  ,   Gallagher  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Stranger","meanings":["English: nickname for a newcomer to an area, from Middle English <i>stra(u)nger(e)</i> ‘stranger, foreigner’ (Old French <i>estrangier</i>). Compare   Strange  ."]},{"name":"Doyle","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Sean, Kieran, Seamus, Aileen, Dermot, Liam, Niall, Brennan, Brigid, Conal, Conan, Donal.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Dubhghaill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Dubhghall</i>’, a personal name composed of the elements <i>dubh</i> ‘black’ + <i>gall</i> ‘stranger’. This was used as a byname for Scandinavians, in particular to distinguish the darker-haired Danes from fair-haired Norwegians. Compare   McDougall  ,   McDowell  ."]},{"name":"Lestrange","meanings":["Irish and English: variant of   Strange   1 with fused Old French definite article <i>le</i>.","Irish: in Ireland, adopted for <b>Mac Conchoigchríche</b> ‘son of <i>Cúchoigcriche</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘hound of the borderland’. <i>Lestrange</i> was adopted for <b>Mac Conchoigchríche</b> probably due to the presence of a prominent family of Lestrange, of similar meaning, who settled in the counties of Westmeath and Offaly in the 16th century."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":73,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":82,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"John Strange was born in 1142, in Shropshire, England as the son of John Strange. He died in 1224, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1142–1224":"1142–1224","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1165–1269":"1165–1269","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1224":"1224","1165":"1165","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1172":"1172","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1142–1224":"1142–1224","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1165–1269":"1165–1269","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1224":"1224","1165":"1165","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1172":"1172","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"1142–1224":"1142–1224","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1165–1269":"1165–1269","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1224":"1224","1165":"1165","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1172":"1172","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"John Strange est né en 1142, à Shropshire, Angleterre, fils de John Strange. Il est décédé en 1224, à l’âge de 82 ans."},"de":{"1142–1224":"1142–1224","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1165–1269":"1165–1269","1120–Male":"1120–Verstorben","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1224":"1224","1165":"1165","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1172":"1172","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","lifeSummary":"John Strange wurde 1142 in Shropshire, England, als Sohn von John Strange geboren. Er starb 1224 im Alter von 82 Jahren."},"ht":{"1142–1224":"1142–1224","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1165–1269":"1165–1269","1120–Male":"1120–Desede","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1224":"1224","1165":"1165","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1172":"1172","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"hu":{"1142–1224":"11